. PriorityQueue
What is PriorityQueue?

PriorityQueue processes elements based on:

PRIORITY instead of insertion order

Smallest element gets highest priority by default

Internal Data Structure

PriorityQueue internally uses:
Binary Heap (Min Heap)
        10
      /    \
    20      30
   /  \
 40   50
 Parent <= Children
 Smallest element always at root.

 Heap internally stored as array:
 Index:  0   1   2   3   4
 Value: 10  20  30  40  50

 Left Child  = 2*i + 1
 Right Child = 2*i + 2
 Parent      = (i-1)/2


 | Feature     | Queue             | Deque          | PriorityQueue    |
 | ----------- | ----------------- | -------------- | ---------------- |
 | Ordering    | FIFO              | Both ends      | Priority         |
 | Internal DS | Linked List/Array | Circular Array | Heap             |
 | Remove      | Front             | Both ends      | Highest priority |
 | Insert      | Rear              | Both ends      | Heap insertion   |
